<div class="comment" id="comment-47764486">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/tom_alexander">tom_alexander</a> 1 day ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">I&#x27;m giving jj a try but one aspect of it I dislike is edits to files are automatically committed, so you need to defensively create empty new commits for your changes. As in, want to browse the repo from a commit 2 weeks ago? Well if you just checkout that commit and then edit a file, you&#x27;ve automatically changed that commit in your repo and rebased everything after it on top of your new changes. So instead you create a new branch off of the old commit and add an empty commit to that branch so any file changes don&#x27;t end up rewriting the past 2 weeks of history. git is much nicer in that I can do whatever I want to the files and it won&#x27;t change the repo until _I tell it to_.</div>
