<div class="comment" id="comment-47764401">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/dgb23">dgb23</a> 1 day ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">The last paragraph might be the most important one:<p>&gt; There&#x27;s one other reason you should be interested in giving jj a try: it has a git compatible backend, and so you can use jj on your own, without requiring anyone else you&#x27;re working with to convert too. This means that there&#x27;s no real downside to giving it a shot; if it&#x27;s not for you, you&#x27;re not giving up all of the history you wrote with it, and can go right back to git with no issues.</div>
